title: Borders, 1950-59-4, 1822
inscribed: Excise stamp on the back reads: "First Account Taken - 307." Inscription encircles crown.
provenance: Unused length from the Royal Pavilion.
creditline: Gift of Brighton Art Gallery and Museum
description: Two identical borders included in one width of papers. Four colors on light tan ground. Stripes in cream and orange-brown in varying widths and tones.
